Key Match Events: David Willey finishes his career with 100 wickets at 29.75 across 73 ODIs
Haris Rauf heaves Chris Woakes into the night sky, before the ball drops into the reliable hands of Ben Stokes
Post-Match Reflections: Both captains are understandably dismayed in their TV briefings
David Willey says in his post-match interview that the tournament hasn't gone to plan for England and that he is immensely proud of every game he's played for the team
Jos Buttler says that today's win means something, but that the victories have been too few and too late, and that the tournament has been a disappointing performance
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play, reducing the game to 20 overs per side
Others: England make do with a disappointing seventh place finish

Pakistan arrive with hopes of doing the unthinkable and breaking into the top four, but that died a death as soon as Jos Buttler called correctly and opted to bat first. Once England had posted 337, the dream was truly over.
